its record Rs\u202f1.19\u202flakh, silver follows amid festive demand and global uncertainty* –\u202fOct\u202f7\u202f2025\u202f06:13\u202fAM\u202fIST  \n- *Varmora promoters buy back 2\u202f% stake from Carlyle* –\u202fOct\u202f7\u202f2025\u202f12:18\u202fAM\u202fIST  \n- *Waaree promoter to give 1\u202f% equity stake to charity* –\u202fOct\u202f7\u202f2025\u202f12:09\u202fAM\u202fIST  \n- *GST\u202f2.0 sparks festive buying boom, leaves automakers & electronics firms scrambling for supply* –\u202fOct\u202f7\u202f2025\u202f06:07\u202fAM\u202fIST  \n- *Master plan in the works to build a brand new city around Navi\u202fMumbai Airport* –\u202fOct\u202f6\u202f2025\u202f11:57\u202fPM\u202fIST  \n- *Dorf\u202fKetal taps global investors for $1.6\u202fbillion to fund Italmatch deal* –\u202fOct\u202f7\u202f2025\u202f06:20\u202fAM\u202fIST  \n- *Demand for smaller homes surges in September quarter: Magicbricks* –\u202fOct\u202f6\u202f2025\u202f11:52\u202fPM\u202fIST  \n- *Jan\u202fAushadhi retailers seek restoration of minimum distance rule* –\u202fRecent  \n- *Ensure Thane bullet train station connectivity to suburban and metro rail networks: Dy\u202fCM\u202fShinde* –\u202fRecent  \n\n**Auto News Highlights**  \n- *GST\u202f2.0 sparks festive buying boom, leaves automakers & electronics firms scrambling for supply* –\u202fOct\u202f7\u202f2025\u202f06:00\u202fAM\u202fIST  \n- *Mercedes‑Benz India records best‑ever September sales because of historic GST reforms* –\u202f4\u202fhours\u202fago  \n- *Mahindra launches new Bolero range, priced between Rs\u202f7.99\u202fto\u202fRs\u202f9.99\u202flakhs* –\u202f6\u202fhours\u202fago  \n- *India’s Sonalika Tractors sets new record with highest‑ever monthly sales of 20,786\u202funits* –\u202f6\u202fhours\u202fago  \n- *On track to achieve 4\u202flakh export mark in FY26: Maruti\u202fSuzuki* –\u202fOct\u202f5\u202f2025  \n\n**Banking/Finance News Highlights**  \n- *Microfinance interest rates continue to climb as credit costs stay hig